In line with the commitment of Osun State Government towards improving the security and welfare of the people, Governor Adegboyega Oyetola has appointed a foremost human rights activist and Chairman, Police Community Relations Committee (PCRC), Comrade Amitolu Shittu, as the Director-General of the newly established Amotekun Corps. He also appointed a trainer and management Consultant, Richard Tinubu as the Director-General of Bureau of Social Services (BOSS). The appointment announced on Friday, through a statement signed by the Chief Press Secretary to the governor, Mr. Ismail Omipidan, indicates that the appointments is with immediate effect. Shittu, 55, is expected to bring his wealth of experience garnered over the decades to bear in the discharge of his new responsibility with absolute loyalty and dedication. Tinubu, also 55, is expected to bring his several years of experience as a management consultant to bear in the discharge of his new assignment. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .